WEBVTT

00:00:01.510 --> 00:00:02.950
On the first day we moved here,</i>

00:00:03.030 --> 00:00:06.450
the residents played a murder-swap
game without me realising it.</i>

00:00:08.200 --> 00:00:10.080
It's easier than doing surgery.

00:00:12.920 --> 00:00:14.330
During our investigation,</i>

00:00:14.570 --> 00:00:18.720
we realised that murders not related
to the game could have happened...</i>

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:21.120
Nana!

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:23.880
But l didn't have time to be sad.</i>

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:24.920
What is this?

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:27.960
Nana...

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:30.880
lt's the last time, please smile.</i>

00:00:31.080 --> 00:00:33.280
You want to say something
to your husband, right?</i>

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:34.840
Shota.

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:38.800
I...

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:47.440
There is something
that l have to do.</i>

00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:49.680
I've brought the new resident here.

00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:53.280
I mainly do research on Al,
artificial intelligence.

00:00:53.480 --> 00:00:54.760
My wife was murdered,

00:00:54.920 --> 00:00:57.120
and l'd like you to
profile the murderer.

00:00:57.200 --> 00:00:58.080
Hey!

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:00.420
You gave my flat's key
to Miss Kinoshita?

00:01:00.580 --> 00:01:02.250
It was Room 304's.

00:01:02.450 --> 00:01:03.290
My flat?

00:01:03.370 --> 00:01:05.270
Miss Kinoshita lives
in Room 401, right?

00:01:07.510 --> 00:01:08.350
What are they?

00:01:08.430 --> 00:01:09.270
"Room 403, Fujii"

00:01:09.350 --> 00:01:10.280
"Room 301, Ono, Room 302, Tezuka"

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:15.990
You're a bit too early.

00:01:17.150 --> 00:01:18.510
At this timing,

00:01:18.750 --> 00:01:21.710
you have already found me?

00:01:22.990 --> 00:01:24.870
Wait, what is going on?

00:01:25.030 --> 00:01:29.030
The one who should tell us
what is going on isn't me, is it,

00:01:29.430 --> 00:01:30.910
murderer?

00:01:33.310 --> 00:01:35.090
What are you talking about, Akane?

00:01:35.170 --> 00:01:36.150
Yomogida!

00:01:37.910 --> 00:01:38.830
You're noisy.

00:01:40.990 --> 00:01:44.910
Come on, don't leave me out!

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:47.870
As you can see,

00:01:48.030 --> 00:01:50.510
l have checked everything here.

00:01:50.590 --> 00:01:52.390
What have you checked?

00:01:53.590 --> 00:01:54.590
For what?

00:01:54.750 --> 00:01:56.190
To pursue the truth.

00:01:56.390 --> 00:01:57.790
By searching rubbish?

00:01:58.590 --> 00:02:00.430
Instead of what people say,

00:02:00.990 --> 00:02:04.710
they hide what they really think
in what they don't say.

00:02:05.110 --> 00:02:07.510
So, instead of what they treasure,

00:02:07.670 --> 00:02:10.550
a person's truth is in
the rubbish they throw away.

00:02:10.870 --> 00:02:14.110
By opening many bags of rubbish,

00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:16.400
l have found you...

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:18.600
murderer.

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:25.440
Now, will the murderer be honest...

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:29.080
and raise their hand?

00:02:46.660 --> 00:02:47.580
What?

00:02:53.940 --> 00:02:59.240
"Your Turn to Kill"

00:02:59.880 --> 00:03:01.440
Did you hear someone else's voice?

00:03:01.760 --> 00:03:03.840
It's a delicate period of time
for Sou!

00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:05.500
Did you plot everything?

00:03:06.090 --> 00:03:07.170
Mrs Akaike!

00:03:07.770 --> 00:03:08.730
Mr Nikaido.

00:03:08.810 --> 00:03:10.810
I'm thinking about something.

00:03:11.530 --> 00:03:14.220
"Episode 12"

00:03:14.540 --> 00:03:15.610
You're joking, right?

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:19.890
Oh, it isn't me. Those...

00:03:22.330 --> 00:03:23.610
"Akane Kinoshita"

00:03:25.450 --> 00:03:26.970
Akane Kinoshita?

00:03:28.450 --> 00:03:29.810
They're all about rubbish.

00:03:29.890 --> 00:03:31.820
Did you write all of them?

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:39.400
You haven't been making sense to me.

00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:42.400
I wanted to see how you'd react

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:46.160
if l said l have checked everything,
so l said it on purpose.

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:48.930
It didn't upset you at all.

00:03:49.090 --> 00:03:51.250
But you surprised me.

00:03:51.370 --> 00:03:52.450
I don't suspect you.

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:53.770
Anyway...

00:03:54.730 --> 00:03:56.410
it isn't okay to do this.

00:03:56.490 --> 00:03:59.250
I've published many stupid books,

00:04:00.050 --> 00:04:03.680
but still,
as a social nonfiction writer,

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:07.520
l do this because l think revealing
the truth is my life's purpose.

00:04:08.480 --> 00:04:10.530
As you're here,
so l'll check with you.

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:16.080
When the police talked to you
about Akaike's murder,

00:04:16.200 --> 00:04:19.840
l somehow heard them say
something like, "Oh, my..."

00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:22.040
ls this the song?

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:27.410
Julia!

00:04:28.730 --> 00:04:29.930
Yes.

00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:35.210
Have you seen a long,
narrow CD like this?

00:04:36.450 --> 00:04:39.490
We, especially Shota...

00:04:40.770 --> 00:04:43.730
are very sad because
someone close to us was killed.

00:04:44.450 --> 00:04:47.690
You said it was your life's purpose,
but it's just for your books.

00:04:47.770 --> 00:04:48.730
I am sorry.

00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:56.610
Of course the people involved
would feel unpleasant,

00:04:57.570 --> 00:05:02.530
but from the real, dark cases,
if we can learn our lesson...

00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:06.450
So have you got a clue
who the murderer is?

00:05:07.810 --> 00:05:10.650
This is embarrassing,
but not at all.

00:05:11.930 --> 00:05:15.600
Did you borrow Room 304's key
to look for the murderer?

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:19.020
Yeah, Ms Kitagawa moved away,

00:05:19.100 --> 00:05:21.140
I didn't think that
there would be any clues,

00:05:21.220 --> 00:05:22.460
but l wanted to check anyway.

00:05:22.540 --> 00:05:24.940
You entered Shota's flat too,
didn't you?

00:05:28.900 --> 00:05:32.940
In other words, you're saying
that l killed his wife?

00:05:33.020 --> 00:05:34.220
This isn't funny.

00:05:37.620 --> 00:05:39.220
Before you suspect someone,

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:42.260
open 100 bags of the rubbish
they threw away.

00:05:44.060 --> 00:05:46.500
This is what <i>Rubbish Writer
Kinoshita</i> said.

00:05:47.540 --> 00:05:50.140
It's okay, Kuroshima. Let's go.

00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:52.100
No, it isn't okay.

00:05:53.500 --> 00:05:55.700
This flat is a treasure house
of data.

00:05:56.180 --> 00:05:57.720
Let's do some treasure hunting.

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:06.600
Was this found in
Sanae Enomoto's flat?

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:12.000
Yes, sir. Yutaro Yamagiwa's DNA
was found on this bath towel.

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:16.120
Was anyone else's DNA
found on this towel?

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:19.000
We found another person's DNA,

00:06:19.200 --> 00:06:21.680
but it isn't a match
with anyone in the Enomoto family.

00:06:22.160 --> 00:06:23.080
Oh?

00:06:24.160 --> 00:06:25.160
What's the matter?

00:06:25.640 --> 00:06:26.840
Nothing, it's just...

00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:28.320
Kamiya.

00:06:29.160 --> 00:06:30.000
Kamiya!

00:06:30.200 --> 00:06:31.960
- Yes, sir?
- Explain.

00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:36.800
Regarding this case,
l have nothing more to add.

00:06:36.920 --> 00:06:40.960
Not this. Room 302's Nana Hosokawa?

00:06:41.080 --> 00:06:42.540
Wait, Hibino?

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:44.300
We use Tezuka for convenience.

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:47.980
I mean Nana Tezuka's call record.

00:06:48.940 --> 00:06:51.380
We still haven't found
Nana Tezuka's mobile,

00:06:51.460 --> 00:06:53.300
but we've gotten the record.

00:06:53.380 --> 00:06:54.700
She talked to Mr Kamiya.

00:06:54.780 --> 00:06:57.300
She sought my advice on something.

00:06:57.420 --> 00:06:59.580
My husband has gone missing
since this morning.

00:06:59.660 --> 00:07:01.380
Is it related to the game?

00:07:01.540 --> 00:07:03.860
She said she couldn't get hold
of Shota Tezuka...

00:07:03.940 --> 00:07:05.870
lt's what you should've
reported first!

00:07:06.470 --> 00:07:07.430
Sorry, sir.

00:07:07.950 --> 00:07:10.790
How long had Nana Tezuka been dead
when her body was found?

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:13.430
It was 29 to 31 hours
after her death.

00:07:13.510 --> 00:07:16.070
Give us your alibi
during that time, idiot.

00:07:16.830 --> 00:07:18.030
Yes, sir. Right away.

00:07:18.630 --> 00:07:22.070
Excuse me, sir,
l've got more to report.

00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.030
What?

00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:26.050
The last call was made
to the nurses station.

00:07:26.250 --> 00:07:28.810
Well, her husband was hospitalised.

00:07:29.050 --> 00:07:32.970
Yes, but it was to
another hospital's nurses station.

00:07:33.050 --> 00:07:34.890
"Nurses Station"

00:07:36.170 --> 00:07:37.370
What the heck?

00:07:37.890 --> 00:07:39.610
That's scary.

00:07:40.450 --> 00:07:41.970
We'll borrow these.

00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:43.410
Give it back afterwards.

00:07:43.490 --> 00:07:45.730
We can't promise you
that we'll give it back.

00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:47.370
They aren't originally yours.

00:07:47.450 --> 00:07:48.810
I know, but...

00:07:53.090 --> 00:07:55.210
Sorry. Thanks.
You have school, right?

00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:57.250
- We'll finish the rest alone.
- But...

00:07:57.690 --> 00:07:58.610
lt's okay.

00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:00.110
Okay.

00:08:07.730 --> 00:08:08.920
"Blender Housewife and
her husband's strange life"

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.920
Every single one of them...

00:08:11.280 --> 00:08:12.700
This is my case.

00:08:16.580 --> 00:08:18.640
I have to go to school too.

00:08:21.920 --> 00:08:23.300
And l didn't sleep.

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:27.980
"2nd April, at collection point
Yoko lshizaki"

00:08:28.060 --> 00:08:29.630
Actually, at that time,

00:08:29.830 --> 00:08:32.270
l wrote my own name down.

00:08:40.990 --> 00:08:41.950
"Sachiko Akaike"

00:08:42.310 --> 00:08:43.590
"Sachiko Akaike."

00:08:43.950 --> 00:08:45.990
lt's the name on
the piece of paper l drew.

00:08:46.070 --> 00:08:47.750
"25th March,
201 Ukita's rubbish bag"

00:08:49.030 --> 00:08:49.910
lnput this...

00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:55.990
What are you doing?

00:08:58.180 --> 00:08:59.030
Nothing.

00:09:01.190 --> 00:09:02.830
Please input them.

00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:08.790
"Paper with Yoko lshizaki written
was thrown away on 2nd April"

00:09:08.870 --> 00:09:10.030
This one too.

00:09:12.350 --> 00:09:14.150
"11th May, 501 Sano's rubbish bag"

00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:17.150
But Sano didn't participate
in the game.

00:09:17.470 --> 00:09:18.590
Input it anyway.

00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:25.910
"Condolence Money Envelope"

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:28.310
"3rd May,
202 Kuroshima's rubbish bag"

00:09:33.550 --> 00:09:37.630
Are you not going to defend me?

00:09:38.150 --> 00:09:42.430
Please tell me the truth,
so that l can defend you.

00:09:44.070 --> 00:09:45.750
When will l be released?

00:09:45.830 --> 00:09:49.470
Damaging and abandoning
a dead body will be about 3 years.

00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:52.230
Sou will be 17 years old
three years later...

00:09:52.350 --> 00:09:55.550
However, if you had also
committed murder...

00:09:55.630 --> 00:09:57.630
How is Sou now?

00:09:57.830 --> 00:09:59.990
You could be charged
for imprisoning Soichi...

00:10:00.070 --> 00:10:02.990
No! l'm asking how his life is now!

00:10:03.070 --> 00:10:06.830
Is Masako
looking after him properly?

00:10:07.070 --> 00:10:09.390
- I think he's fine.
- l don't care what you think!

00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:12.150
Things are now...

00:10:12.750 --> 00:10:15.510
very delicate... for Sou now...

00:10:15.590 --> 00:10:16.670
He's a teenager.

00:10:16.990 --> 00:10:18.710
So, about Yamagiwa's murder...

00:10:18.790 --> 00:10:21.070
Yamagiwa doesn't matter at all!

00:10:29.430 --> 00:10:32.630
Sorry to have kept you waiting.

00:10:32.710 --> 00:10:33.550
It's okay.

00:10:33.950 --> 00:10:36.230
I only brought some stuff
for your parents,

00:10:36.350 --> 00:10:40.030
but they inspected my belongings
for some reason.

00:10:40.190 --> 00:10:41.790
Because you look funny.

00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:42.790
What?

00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:46.630
Do you mean suspicious
or interesting?

00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:50.190
If you mean interesting,
l'll forgive you!

00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:54.230
Don't look so serious, teenager,
or l'll kiss you on the cheek.

00:10:54.310 --> 00:10:55.510
Let's go home.

00:10:55.910 --> 00:10:57.630
Hey!

00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:00.060
"Tsutsuji Elderly Home"

00:11:00.380 --> 00:11:03.580
Oh? Mrs Sachiko seems to be
in a good mood today.

00:11:04.100 --> 00:11:05.490
Yes, thank you.

00:11:14.510 --> 00:11:15.350
What's the matter?

00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:18.750
You want to watch it?

00:11:19.270 --> 00:11:20.710
Wait a minute.

00:11:22.910 --> 00:11:24.030
There you go.

00:11:36.080 --> 00:11:39.150
- Thank you! Thank you!
- He always sings this.

00:11:39.830 --> 00:11:44.630
Thank you for this year too.
l sang my favourite song.

00:11:44.950 --> 00:11:46.910
Thank you-- ls he sleeping?

00:11:48.270 --> 00:11:50.150
Okay, who requested...

00:11:51.590 --> 00:11:53.070
He took my mic!

00:11:59.710 --> 00:12:04.830
Oh, my Julia!

00:12:06.030 --> 00:12:07.150
Mrs Akaike!

00:12:19.750 --> 00:12:23.590
I feel guilty for coming every time
l want to deduce something.

00:12:23.790 --> 00:12:25.630
I don't mind, though.

00:12:26.390 --> 00:12:27.670
But l'll let you decide.

00:12:28.870 --> 00:12:30.750
In that case, l'll borrow it.

00:12:31.030 --> 00:12:32.110
Will you help me?

00:12:34.150 --> 00:12:35.830
Why are you doing that again, Doyan?

00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:37.190
Well...

00:12:38.150 --> 00:12:40.190
please don't call me that.

00:12:40.310 --> 00:12:43.070
But you hate your first name, right?
So you're Doyan.

00:12:43.390 --> 00:12:44.600
Come on, please.

00:12:45.400 --> 00:12:46.400
We'll borrow this.

00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:49.560
Be careful.

00:12:52.860 --> 00:12:53.700
What's this?

00:12:54.300 --> 00:12:55.280
Well...

00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:58.600
Could this be
the Fibonacci sequence?

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.360
Yes, l love it.

00:13:01.600 --> 00:13:02.600
"Bochi" what?

00:13:02.800 --> 00:13:03.900
- Fibonacci.
- Fibonacci.

00:13:07.140 --> 00:13:09.140
Oh. What's that?

00:13:09.420 --> 00:13:10.380
Well...

00:13:21.750 --> 00:13:22.590
lt's this.

00:13:23.110 --> 00:13:25.310
I can stare at
this equation forever.

00:13:25.470 --> 00:13:26.480
Yeah.

00:13:28.600 --> 00:13:30.620
I think you should explain it
with a diagram.

00:13:31.740 --> 00:13:34.030
First, the Fibonacci sequence

00:13:34.110 --> 00:13:36.310
is like the
ammonite shell's structure...

00:13:36.990 --> 00:13:37.990
lt's all right.

00:13:38.350 --> 00:13:40.830
You science people
can get excited about it.

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:44.870
Doyan, what do people call you?

00:13:45.110 --> 00:13:46.310
Just Nikaido.

00:13:46.390 --> 00:13:48.230
What? lt's so boring.

00:13:56.510 --> 00:13:58.140
Thank you for this morning.

00:13:58.260 --> 00:14:00.740
Please tell me if you remember
anything else.

00:14:01.540 --> 00:14:03.620
It's okay, don't bother.

00:14:07.380 --> 00:14:10.550
"Xinyi, Misato and Goro Akaike"

00:14:21.870 --> 00:14:23.510
We can't hide anymore!

00:14:23.630 --> 00:14:24.470
What's the matter?

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:26.510
Those guys have investigated a lot.

00:14:26.670 --> 00:14:28.910
It's a matter of time
that they find out!

00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:30.310
What are you talking about?

00:14:30.390 --> 00:14:31.590
Mr Tezuka and his friends

00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:34.170
wrote things about the game
on the whiteboard,

00:14:34.650 --> 00:14:37.290
and it says l killed
Mr and Mrs Akaike!

00:14:39.050 --> 00:14:40.290
That's...

00:14:44.130 --> 00:14:45.130
They guessed wrong.

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:47.890
Yeah, they guessed wrong, but...

00:14:47.970 --> 00:14:48.810
lt's okay, then.

00:14:48.890 --> 00:14:52.130
But if they have dug so deep,

00:14:52.330 --> 00:14:55.840
they'll find out about you
and our friends' visa!

00:15:21.800 --> 00:15:22.840
Mr Tamiya...

00:15:25.200 --> 00:15:26.240
Nana...

00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:30.120
And Mrs lshizaki too.

00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:32.040
"Yoko lshizaki"

00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:33.120
Really?

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:37.960
See? That means
Mrs lshizaki didn't lie.

00:15:38.680 --> 00:15:41.800
Of course, it isn't
entirely impossible that

00:15:42.040 --> 00:15:45.680
someone made a fake one
and threw it away.

00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:50.400
And Mr Ukita didn't lie either.

00:15:50.880 --> 00:15:52.000
Also...

00:15:52.360 --> 00:15:53.810
After what happened,

00:15:54.770 --> 00:15:56.370
we can be sure about this too.

00:15:56.730 --> 00:15:58.570
"Yutaro Yamagiwa"

00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:02.170
"Sanae Enomoto:
Paper drawn: Yutaro Yamagiwa"

00:16:02.250 --> 00:16:05.890
Looking at this,
we haven't made much progress.

00:16:07.050 --> 00:16:07.990
No.

00:16:09.770 --> 00:16:14.290
Also, Miss Kinoshita took this too.

00:16:14.730 --> 00:16:17.770
Kuroshima, she got it from
a bag of your rubbish.

00:16:18.490 --> 00:16:19.770
Do you remember this?

00:16:21.250 --> 00:16:22.530
I...

00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:23.890
Will you answer me right away?

00:16:24.330 --> 00:16:27.250
If you think too long, l'd think
that you're concocting a lie.

00:16:28.930 --> 00:16:29.770
Sure.

00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:35.170
My last boyfriend passed away.

00:16:36.170 --> 00:16:37.010
What?

00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:40.290
I used it for his funeral.

00:16:41.610 --> 00:16:44.320
I think you met him once.

00:16:44.830 --> 00:16:47.290
- Where's the convenience store?
- l don't know.

00:16:47.370 --> 00:16:50.890
Go to the main road and turn right.
lt's just 100 metres away.

00:16:53.850 --> 00:16:57.010
He got drunk
and had a fight with a stranger,

00:16:57.890 --> 00:16:58.930
and suddenly...

