Even if we had,
l had no idea who you were.

00:37:33.180 --> 00:37:34.140
Hello?

00:37:35.300 --> 00:37:36.140
Oh?

00:37:36.620 --> 00:37:38.020
Oh, l'm sorry.

00:37:38.940 --> 00:37:40.890
I was thinking about something.

00:37:40.970 --> 00:37:42.620
About Shota?

00:37:42.700 --> 00:37:43.900
No...

00:37:44.620 --> 00:37:45.580
May l?

00:37:52.780 --> 00:37:53.980
Wait!

00:37:59.620 --> 00:38:00.740
What's the matter?

00:38:05.860 --> 00:38:08.020
Sorry, l have to do a presentation.

00:38:37.300 --> 00:38:38.340
Soichi?

00:38:40.300 --> 00:38:41.140
Sawa!

00:38:41.780 --> 00:38:42.740
A cat?

00:38:44.180 --> 00:38:45.140
Is that...

00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:49.020
He doesn't move.
Do you know where the hospital is?

00:38:55.900 --> 00:39:00.060
But l think he's dead.

00:39:03.700 --> 00:39:05.020
Don't cry.

00:39:07.540 --> 00:39:08.620
Well...

00:39:11.460 --> 00:39:12.860
Let's bury him somewhere.

00:39:14.180 --> 00:39:15.580
- Okay?
- Okay.

00:39:16.780 --> 00:39:17.660
Let's go.

00:39:29.980 --> 00:39:34.030
You shouldn't take him around
at such a late hour.

00:39:34.270 --> 00:39:35.510
I am very sorry.

00:39:35.830 --> 00:39:36.670
But auntie...

00:39:36.750 --> 00:39:37.750
Oh? Soichi?

00:39:38.710 --> 00:39:40.790
I heard you were staying at
an orphanage!

00:39:40.990 --> 00:39:41.990
I am sorry.

00:39:42.390 --> 00:39:46.110
I thought you knew.
He has started going to school.

00:39:46.190 --> 00:39:49.200
I didn't... What a surprise!

00:39:49.520 --> 00:39:52.180
You were in the room
with him, weren't you?

00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:53.820
Yes.

00:39:53.900 --> 00:39:55.260
I am sorry,

00:39:55.500 --> 00:39:58.620
l didn't want him to see
anyone involved in the case,

00:39:58.780 --> 00:40:00.740
so l didn't let him
go and say hello.

00:40:00.820 --> 00:40:01.740
Okay.

00:40:02.180 --> 00:40:03.140
I am sorry.

00:40:03.220 --> 00:40:05.940
You are fine, because you're cute.

00:40:06.580 --> 00:40:09.270
But l would like to ask
you something.

00:40:10.070 --> 00:40:11.510
Not about the case.

00:40:11.590 --> 00:40:12.470
Okay.

00:40:12.790 --> 00:40:15.590
- When we were imprisoned,
- l said no!

00:40:15.670 --> 00:40:19.870
Did you hear another person's voice
besides your dad's and your mum's?

00:40:21.150 --> 00:40:22.950
I make my decisions quickly.

00:40:27.590 --> 00:40:30.110
I don't really know.

00:40:31.750 --> 00:40:33.630
- I see.
- That's enough!

00:40:33.730 --> 00:40:35.250
Let's stop here.

00:40:40.890 --> 00:40:45.050
There was definitely
a third person's voice.

00:40:45.770 --> 00:40:47.770
I told the police too.

00:40:54.810 --> 00:40:56.220
Oh, it's Doyan.

00:40:56.820 --> 00:40:59.700
What will we have
for supper tonight?

00:41:03.460 --> 00:41:04.420
Hello.

00:41:04.820 --> 00:41:06.660
May l talk to you for a bit?

00:41:10.180 --> 00:41:11.620
See? l knew it!

00:41:12.020 --> 00:41:13.260
What do you know?

00:41:13.380 --> 00:41:16.560
All these towels belong to
the Enomoto family, right?

00:41:17.080 --> 00:41:19.240
Have you realised something?

00:41:19.320 --> 00:41:20.160
No.

00:41:20.240 --> 00:41:22.340
They are all camel!

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:24.280
Indeed, they are all beige.

00:41:24.400 --> 00:41:25.840
Indeed, they are beige.

00:41:25.920 --> 00:41:27.160
What about beige?

00:41:27.960 --> 00:41:29.520
You call it beige too.

00:41:30.040 --> 00:41:34.250
And this is the bath towel that
we found Yamagiwa's DNA on.

00:41:34.930 --> 00:41:36.170
It's purple?

00:41:36.610 --> 00:41:40.530
This towel doesn't belong to
the Enomoto family, does it?

00:41:41.010 --> 00:41:41.850
I see.

00:41:42.410 --> 00:41:44.650
If we dig further along that line,

00:41:44.890 --> 00:41:48.170
maybe we will find out
who the other DNA belongs to.

00:41:48.250 --> 00:41:50.490
I've got something
that might cause a stir.

00:41:50.570 --> 00:41:51.410
What is it?

00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:53.010
It isn't related to our case,

00:41:53.130 --> 00:41:55.650
but the suspects of the murder of
Yoshihiko Hakamada were narrowed down

00:41:55.730 --> 00:41:57.370
and they've searched
all over the country.

00:41:58.330 --> 00:42:00.290
They seem gentle though.

00:42:03.170 --> 00:42:05.130
"Profiling Results"

00:42:05.210 --> 00:42:06.130
What do you mean?

00:42:06.210 --> 00:42:10.410
For example, most of
the Japanese people are this tall,

00:42:10.970 --> 00:42:13.650
which means we don't know anything.

00:42:13.970 --> 00:42:15.770
Why do you show me this?

00:42:16.210 --> 00:42:17.370
I just want to.

00:42:17.930 --> 00:42:20.200
You seem to expect too much from Al,

00:42:20.560 --> 00:42:23.920
so l should tell you how little
the data we now have can do.

00:42:27.280 --> 00:42:29.480
What about "committed by
the same murderer" here?

00:42:29.640 --> 00:42:30.890
It's the probability that

00:42:30.970 --> 00:42:34.810
Nana and the other victims here were
killed by the same person.

00:42:35.610 --> 00:42:39.010
But l have too little data about
this too and l can't say anything.

00:42:39.450 --> 00:42:42.090
Did the data about
Ono and Fujii help?

00:42:43.170 --> 00:42:45.570
Somehow you look scary.

00:42:45.770 --> 00:42:47.690
We found that
the chemical used to kill her

00:42:47.770 --> 00:42:50.050
was pharmaceutical
potassium chloride.

00:42:50.450 --> 00:42:52.290
Well, l doubt it.

00:42:52.530 --> 00:42:54.450
Especially in Dr Fujii's case...

00:42:54.530 --> 00:42:55.450
What?

00:42:55.730 --> 00:42:58.210
Potassium chloride
was what killed her.

00:42:58.810 --> 00:43:02.650
If we let the Al analyse it
when we have so few samples,

00:43:03.450 --> 00:43:05.010
it'll say Fujii is the murderer.

00:43:06.410 --> 00:43:08.820
I thought Fujii was suspicious too.

00:43:09.460 --> 00:43:12.180
It is a chemical that
a doctor can easily get.

00:43:12.260 --> 00:43:15.920
We use the Al to avoid
simple guesses like this.

00:43:22.620 --> 00:43:24.780
Thank you. See you tomorrow.

00:43:25.220 --> 00:43:26.060
Okay.

00:43:26.140 --> 00:43:27.260
Good night.

00:43:35.540 --> 00:43:37.860
I have to eliminate
the possibility one by one.

00:43:39.260 --> 00:43:40.300
Right, Nana?

00:43:47.820 --> 00:43:50.820
You come here every day.
This isn't right.

00:43:51.500 --> 00:43:52.460
Wait...

00:43:53.020 --> 00:43:55.060
Hey... What are you doing?

00:44:00.100 --> 00:44:01.060
What are you doing?

00:44:01.140 --> 00:44:02.700
Looking for evidence.

00:44:02.780 --> 00:44:03.900
That's trespassing!

00:44:03.980 --> 00:44:05.700
It is. Please call the police.

00:44:05.780 --> 00:44:06.940
I will!

00:44:07.540 --> 00:44:09.820
I'll call the police!
They'll be here at once!

00:44:09.900 --> 00:44:11.500
You'll be in trouble!

00:44:11.580 --> 00:44:16.560
Then, l'll say to them,
"This guy killed Nana!"

00:44:16.640 --> 00:44:20.000
The police will search your flat.
Are you okay with that?

00:44:20.640 --> 00:44:21.520
With what?

00:44:21.880 --> 00:44:24.440
Will you really be okay
even if they search your flat?

00:44:26.720 --> 00:44:27.800
Yeah, l will.

00:44:28.600 --> 00:44:31.240
You talk like a child when you lie.

00:44:35.560 --> 00:44:38.400
Hey! Wait... No! Hang on...

00:44:46.500 --> 00:44:47.340
Oh?

00:44:48.220 --> 00:44:50.420
Oh, gosh! lt isn't my fault, okay?

00:44:52.660 --> 00:44:54.140
We've got some breaking news.

00:44:54.340 --> 00:44:55.340
This May,

00:44:55.420 --> 00:44:59.500
Actor Yoshihiko Hakamada was killed
in a mountain in Tochigi Prefecture,

00:44:59.580 --> 00:45:02.380
and photos of the murder suspects
have been released.

00:45:09.780 --> 00:45:13.780
The wanted men are
an Iranian man Ali Moharrami

00:45:13.900 --> 00:45:14.720
and an American...

00:45:29.410 --> 00:45:30.570
This is Kuroshima.

00:45:30.650 --> 00:45:32.610
Shota, can you watch the TV now?

00:45:32.890 --> 00:45:34.640
Please call back
when you hear my message.

00:45:35.160 --> 00:45:36.500
Stop it.

00:45:39.500 --> 00:45:40.500
No...

00:45:40.580 --> 00:45:42.300
lt's getting more and more serious

00:45:42.380 --> 00:45:44.020
and l don't know
what they're saying.

00:45:45.980 --> 00:45:48.940
"Your Turn to Kill"

00:45:49.020 --> 00:45:51.900
l am Minami and
l've moved to Room 502.

00:45:51.980 --> 00:45:53.380
What a nuisance.

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:54.740
He had a smile on his face.

00:45:54.820 --> 00:45:55.700
In details!

00:45:55.820 --> 00:45:56.820
I'll say everything.

00:45:56.900 --> 00:45:57.900
I beat him with a hammer.

00:45:57.980 --> 00:45:59.660
When will this stop?

00:45:59.860 --> 00:46:01.380
About Miss Kuroshima.

00:46:01.460 --> 00:46:02.860
She is strange.

00:46:02.940 --> 00:46:03.860
Why?